  Adaon nods, and says, "Ah, >politics<.  Aye, I know about >politics<.  
I know enough about it to say I hate em.  We >bards< are 
nonpolitical, for the most part.  Our system o' >rank< reflects that.  
Any that reach Anstruth be guild masters, and that be that.  No 
special requirements, no special responsibilities.  We figure that if ye 
made it that far, ye likely had help, so ye must have friends that 
respect ye.  There's nothin' ye can do to force people to give ye 
respect; if ye can earn it then ye deserve it.
  "Now, I not be sayin' it's useless to advance within the guild 
structure; that's not true.  It's just that there be no pressure upon ye 
to do so.  Oh, there be a few bonuses to achievin' such status, like the 
increased training ye receive, but there is not the emphasis on
guildmastership here that other guilds have.  We're more easy-going,
I suppose ye might say."
  Adaon looks thoughtfully off into space then.
